{
  "texts": [
    "Transparent reporting of prompts, model versions, and design choices will be critical for building a cumulative and credible body of research.",
    "Re-imagining Lasswell's 5Ws with LLMsHarold Lasswell's classic model-\"Who says what, in which channel, to whom, with what effect?",
    "\"-has long provided a foundational structure for communication research.",
    "While often debated and expanded upon, its core dimensions continue to frame inquiries into media content, audience response, and message effects.",
    "The emergence of LLMs offers a unique opportunity to revisit each of these components with new methodological tools."
  ]
}